Manchester United goalkeeper David de Gea took to Twitter on Wednesday night to show his support to injured Stoke striker Bojan Krkic.

The 24-year-old suffered a cruciate knee injury in his side's FA Cup win against Rochdale on Monday night - ruling him out for the rest of the season as a result.

And friend and former Spain Under 21 team-mate De Gea took to the social networking site to post a selfie of the pair together, while wishing him the best for his recovery ahead.

